Home Page




“A line of inquiry is a set of questions that you are trying to answer through reading and research  design+creative practice. They are questions that you might already have a partial answer to but that you would like to pursue further.”



Lines of Inquiry is an exhibition about the questions, probes, investigations that we pursue as designers. It explores How as designers we may move from solving problems to framing them? How might we use design as a medium to ask questions that we feel are important? How do our personal curiosities find their way into our practice?



What is a Project?

A project is widely understood as an outcome oriented exercise taken up in an academic setting, we want to re-define it as an inquiry driven exercise which uses design as a tool to probe, investigate and question. 

When does a project become an Inquiry?

When you start framing your own questions, the project becomes an Inquiry


What are we looking for?

Inquiries which are personal
Inquiries which are professional

Inquires which question the familiar
Inquiries which chart into the unfamiliar

Inquiries about the mundane
Inquiries about the exciting

Inquiries which are small
Inquiries which are big
We are looking for any and all projects which ask your questions through your practice.
